# Version update workflow

**All version updates must go through review changes.** Do not commit or push version bumps.

1. Run the version-bump script (or update version files manually) so the new version is reflected everywhere and the archive is built.
2. Leave the changes unstaged/uncommitted so the user can **review the diff**.
3. The **user** will commit and push when ready.

Do not run `git add`, `git commit`, or `git push` for version updates.
